Outdated Source syntax - needs update to Source[FORMAT]

This test uses bare `Source` type without the phantom format annotation:
  ~event compile { code: Source }

Modern syntax uses Source[FORMAT] to indicate the source format:
  ~event compile { code: Source[KORU] }

The generated code also has issues - it expects .source but params are named
'code' and 'template'. We should be able to support arbitrarily named `Source`-parameter
names, but the syntax for filling it out when invoking is different from the inline implicit 
Source-parameter syntax. 

Related: Test 210_021 (source_phantom_syntax) is also broken.

Fix: Update to use proper Source[FORMAT] syntax or delete if redundant with
other Source tests in the suite.
